channel.description:
It was well done but it has been proven as a hoax by RTL. (Whatever that is)
Here's the video: (Are the Youtube Tags back?)
[url]https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=qOCO3qsQMTg[/url]
[youtube]https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=qOCO3qsQMTg[/youtube] [yt]https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=qOCO3qsQMTg[/yt] [b]Clearly not.[/b][/size]
Default Michael Jackson IS ALIVE! Check the video for yourself and give me your thoughts mine are below it:
IMPORTANT NOTICE: No media files are hosted on these forums. By clicking the link below you agree to view content from an external website. We can not be held responsible for the suitability or legality of this material. I AGREE
My Thoughts: I saw the video on this website: [url='https://www.michaeljacksonhoaxdeath.com/']Michael Jackson Death Hoax[/url]
Its a good site, full of theories but whether or not this is fake, what we need to remember is that MJ is dead as far as his life is concerned, maybe he is on an island with Tupac but he wants to be there for a reason. The evidence in the below picture shows this video is fake:
[img]https://cds058.lo1.hwcdn.net/e3m9u5m8/cds/s/14/media14/2009/Aug/25/LiveLeak-dot-com-72bad5db444e-mj_zombie1.jpg?doppl=1054e42e5ac34dce5a934d9e1f83f5b3ce46fe3d&dopsig=60933e1754ac6d3c8e5f891c031e3ea6[/img]
As you can see the van on the left has a sticker below the registeration/license plate and the van on the right doesn't. Also the FORD badge is not in the same place as the image on the left. RTL have said it was fake and that it was made to see how many people would believe it, now I think its fake but what do you think?
